-- Bank of Canada Buys C$1 Billion of Securities for One Day
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-03-28T18:46:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-28/bank-of-canada-buys-c-1-billion-of-securities-for-one-day-1-.html
The  Bank of Canada  bought C$1.001
billion ($985 million) of securities for one day.  The central bank announced the purchase, aimed to keep
overnight lending rates close to its current target of 1
percent, on its website today from Ottawa. Earlier today it
announced initial buying of C$560 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
